node.text: Well, this is an odd one. Think this might be my first #SomewhereToGo post in over a year. This weekend I produced/ADed a short film (@justthisoncefilm) and met some incredible people, including @noahawatersiii here, who despite not wearing any literal hats, wore a lot of hats. And no, we didn’t coordinate (but FUCK do we look cool).

node.text:
Outfit #26: Let me level with you, this bodysuit is cute as hell but THE WHOLE SHOOT it was desperately trying to achieve its lifelong dream of being a waist belt. I know you guys are bored of seeing me stare longingly into different distances so I made a stupid thing for you at the end instead of finding ways to actually be funny⁣
⁣
(Ps I finally figured out the remote control for this thing and my life is now 50x easier)⁣
⁣
New project coming soon?

node.text: Admittedly, this is not quite one of my #NowhereToGo series because @alyssajrose was the one to make my ghost dog dreams a reality with her amazing outdoor backdrop. I titled this phone album “Ghost Dog Chaos” which I feel is fitting, as this first picture was the only usable shot out of 200. Nevertheless, they were VERY GOOD DOGS and I was very impressed with their professionalism. Swipe for TONS OF GHOST DOG CHAOS
